You are an AI assistant for the Common Secretary Services project.

Project Overview:
- Python-based service for automated processing of audio, video, and other media files
- Focus on transcription and structured output using templates
- Built with Flask/Flask-RESTX for the API layer
- Uses OpenAI GPT-4 for transcription and text processing

Key Components:
1. Audio Processing
   - Multiple format support (MP3, WAV, M4A, etc.)
   - Automatic segmentation
   - Noise reduction and normalization
   - GPT-4 based transcription

2. YouTube Integration
   - Video download and audio extraction
   - Metadata processing
   - Format optimization
   - Rate limiting and size restrictions

3. Template System
   - Markdown-based templates
   - Variable substitution
   - Multiple document types (Meeting, YouTube, Notes)
   - Metadata handling

4. API Layer
   - RESTful endpoints
   - Rate limiting
   - File upload handling
   - Async processing

5. Storage & Processing
   - Temporary file management
   - Cleanup strategies
   - Resource tracking
   - Error handling

Development Guidelines:
- Follow PEP 8 style guide
- Write comprehensive docstrings
- Include type hints
- Add tests for new features
- Document API changes
- Handle errors gracefully

File Structure:
- src/: Source code
  - api/: API implementation
  - processors/: Media processors
  - core/: Core functionality
  - utils/: Utilities
- docs/: Documentation
- tests/: Test files
- templates/: Markdown templates
- config/: Configuration files

Common Tasks:
1. Audio Processing:
   - File validation
   - Format conversion
   - Segmentation
   - Transcription

2. Template Usage:
   - Variable replacement
   - Markdown generation
   - Metadata handling
   - Output formatting

3. Error Handling:
   - Input validation
   - Process monitoring
   - Error recovery
   - User feedback

4. Configuration:
   - Environment variables
   - YAML configuration
   - API keys
   - Processing parameters

